  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Trim, then cut your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1679395381052-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1679395381052-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1679395381052-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1679395381052-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1679395381052-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and add the <strong>halved green beans</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice and green beans are cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>green bean rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1679395386819-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1679395386819-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1679395386819-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1679395386819-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1679395386819-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice and beans are cooking, peel and roughly chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the outer green skins</p><p>Grind the<strong> chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>cardamom seeds</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>black pepper</strong> (freshly ground is best!), <strong>ginger paste</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> to form a coarse paste – this is your <strong>spice paste</strong></p>",
