    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped chicken</strong>, <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>spice paste</strong> to a bowl and mix thoroughly – this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>chicken </strong>and cook, covered, for 4-5 min or until nicely browned</p>",
      "order": 4,
